<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5264&amp;p=31203#p31203"><![CDATA[
I don't think they had image emblem feature back then.<br /><br />Pipalou50 would have changed the font for the user name. <br />That's done by opening up the skin file with Resource Hacker.<br /><br />User_font=&quot;Segoe UI&quot;,normal,22 to whatever font you have in your system.<br />The type of font, and size can put the name placement out of bounds, (get cut off, or sit on top of user picture).<br /><br />Use this help font topic for more info.<br /><br /><!-- l --><a class="postlink-local" href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=2051">viewtopic.php?f=7&amp;t=2051</a><!-- l --><br /><br /><br />Some newer menus allow a user picture area to become invisible using transparent png image. <br />Picture is inputted under the General Behavior tab. Look for User picture text.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Tue Jan 10, 2017 8:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
