<author><name><![CDATA[juniper7]]></name></author>
<updated>2015-11-01T12:25:07-07:00</updated>
<published>2015-11-01T12:25:07-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5264&amp;p=23232#p23232</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5264&amp;p=23232#p23232"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Two Tone (Windows 7 style) and (Classic 1 &amp; 2 column)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5264&amp;p=23232#p23232"><![CDATA[
2 Tone Convert (Classic style) <br /><br />Hi Pipalou50.<br />I skipped working on the original Two Tone (Classic style).<br />Instead, did a slightly faster way, by renaming the file Two Tone &quot;skin.7&quot; to &quot;skin&quot;.<br />Then just fixed a number of things to make it work in classic style. <br />Until I realized I forgot all the one column Classic info needed too. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> Took a long time.<br />I think most of the bugs have been squished. <br /><br />Some things can't be carried over properly, like search box. The inside box color can transfer, but as far as I know,<br />can't make the frame white. So, chop-chop. <br /><br />About the user picture outside. From what Ivo writes about, the user picture in Win 7 style,<br />is a separate window and will have nice smooth corners.<br />But in Classic style, not the case. A bigger main menu, with a transparent top has to be used, which follows the opacity of main menu. If it is alpha, then user picture 1/2 outside corners will look smooth,<br />just have to turn off the menu shadow in csm settings.<br /><br />But if skin instructs CSM to use glass, artifacts (dark edge pixels, residual glass color breakthrough), appear around the user picture. See the picture from earlier post. As well as top menu flashing, when animated menu opened. <br />So I turned off glass, when the picture 1/2 outside, switches to alpha mode. More chop chop!<br /><br />So compromises were made here and there, and the color tones are different from original Two Tone classic,<br />as well as separator lines put back in. As one of my past work bosses said, &quot;Nothing sits, everything changes&quot;.<br /><br />Ooh yeah, If you want to have a transparent surrounding user picture, Ivo mentioned a simple way, as what is in his &quot;Metro&quot; skin. <br />Instead of using the default Windows user picture, <br />one can override that picture with one of your own transparent background 32 bit.bmp, .png image.<br />Go to &quot;General Behavior&quot; User Picture. <br />It works best picking the square option in the skin, as it's picture won't get cut off at the corners. <br /><br /><br /><br />I am sorry, I made so many words to translate back into French. Hope you understand some of it. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Sun Nov 01, 2015 12:25 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
